import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', kde=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cx?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='cx', y='cy', hue='name', palette='viridis')
    max_cx_location = data.loc[data['cx'].idxmax()]['name']
    max_cx_value = data['cx'].max()
    plt.axvline(max_cx_value, linestyle='--', color='red', label=f'{max_cx_location}: {max_cx_value:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which location has the highest cx value?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='cx', y='cy', hue='name', palette='viridis')
    max_cy_location = data.loc[data['cy'].idxmax()]
    plt.axhline(max_cy_location['cy'], color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"{max_cy_location['name']} (cy: {max_cy_location['cy']:.2f})")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which location has the highest cy value?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
